.TH DRIFT 1 "2026-07-23" "drift 0.9.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
drift \- developer-focused context switch tracker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B drift
.RI [ COMMAND ]
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B drift
tracks your active window/app, detects context switches, quantifies focus
loss, and shows you exactly how much your attention is drifting.
.PP
It polls your active window every N seconds (default 2), classifies it into
a category (code, distraction, communication, research, system, other),
and records activities, switches, and focus sessions. The focus score
(0\[en]100) is calculated from distraction ratio, focus loss, and switch
count. Context switch cost defaults to 23 minutes based on research,
adjusted by switch type.
.PP
Supported platforms:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Linux: x11rb + xdotool fallback
.IP \(bu 2
macOS: Cocoa/objc
.IP \(bu 2
Windows: Win32 API
.RE
.SH COMMANDS
.SS drift init
Interactive setup wizard. Creates a default config and database.
.SS drift track [\-i SECS] [\-a]
Start the foreground tracker. Blocks the terminal.
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-interval SECS
Polling interval in seconds (default: 2).
.TP
.B \-a, \-\-alert
Enable desktop alerts on distraction (rate limited: 1 per 5 min).
.SS drift daemon start|stop|status [\-i SECS] [\-a]
Background daemon with PID file management.
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-interval SECS
Polling interval in seconds (default: 2).
.TP
.B \-a, \-\-alert
Enable desktop alerts on distraction.
.SS drift status [\-\-json]
Show today's focus summary.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output as JSON (for scripting/piping).
.SS drift report [\-d YYYY-MM-DD]
Generate a daily report with categories, switches, and insights.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-date DATE
Date in YYYY-MM-DD format (default: today).
.SS drift week
Generate a weekly report (last 7 days) with trend comparison.
.SS drift summary [\-d N]
Show N-day summary with daily averages and trend indicators.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-days N
Number of days to show (default: 14).
.SS drift timeline [\-d YYYY-MM-DD]
Show an hourly ASCII bar chart of the day with per-category breakdowns.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-date DATE
Date in YYYY-MM-DD format (default: today).
.SS drift avg
Show rolling averages across 7-day, 14-day, and 30-day windows.
.SS drift insights
Show 7-day pattern analysis: best focus hours, top distractions.
.SS drift compare [\-\-date1 X \-\-date2 Y] [\-\-week]
Compare two days or two weeks.
.TP
.B \-\-date1 DATE
First date for comparison (YYYY-MM-DD).
.TP
.B \-\-date2 DATE
Second date for comparison (YYYY-MM-DD).
.TP
.B \-\-week
Compare this week vs last week.
.SS drift streaks [\-d N]
Show streak history with progress bars.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-days N
Number of days to show (default: 7).
.SS drift goals [show|set KEY VALUE]
Show or set daily goals. Trackable metrics: focus time, context switches,
distraction minutes.
.SS drift log [\-d DATE] [\-c CAT] [\-S] [\-n N]
Show raw activity or switch logs.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-date DATE
Date in YYYY-MM-DD format (default: today).
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-category CAT
Filter by category.
.TP
.B \-S, \-\-switches
Show switches instead of activities.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-limit N
Number of entries to show (default: 50).
.SS drift focus N
Start an N-minute focus session with switch tracking.
.SS drift watch
Live active window monitor with color-coded categories.
.SS drift show
Open the TUI dashboard.
.SS drift export \-f json|csv [\-d DATE]
Export data as JSON or CSV.
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-format FORMAT
Output format: json or csv (default: json).
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-date DATE
Date in YYYY-MM-DD format (default: today).
.SS drift config show|edit|path [KEY] [VALUE]
View and modify config.
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B show
\(em print current config
.IP \(bu 2
.B edit KEY VALUE
\(em set a config key
.IP \(bu 2
.B path
\(em print config file path
.RE
.SS drift ignore add|remove|list [APP]
Manage ignored apps via .driftignore.
.SS drift preset development|writing|research
Apply a config preset.
.SS drift presets
List available config presets.
.SS drift doctor
Run diagnostics: config validity, database health, daemon status, tracker
platform, and display output.
.SS drift reset [\-\-yes]
Wipe all tracking data. Prompts for confirmation unless \-\-yes is given.
.TP
.B \-\-yes
Skip confirmation prompt.
.SS drift completions bash|zsh|fish|powershell
Generate shell completion scripts.
.SS drift export-config [\-o FILE]
Export config as JSON to stdout or a file.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output PATH
Output file path (default: stdout).
.SS drift import PATH
Import config from a JSON file.
.SH CONFIG
Configuration lives at
.I ~/.config/drift/config.toml.
.PP
Key fields:
.PP
.RS
.nf
poll_interval_secs = 2
switching_cost_mins = 23
streak_goal_mins = 90

[categories]
code = ["code", "vim", "neovim", "terminal", "cursor", "zed"]
distraction = ["twitter", "youtube", "reddit", "discord"]
communication = ["slack", "teams", "zoom", "telegram"]
research = ["firefox", "chrome", "brave", "safari"]
system = ["finder", "nautilus", "explorer", "settings"]

ignored_apps = ["screensaver"]
focus_block = ["discord", "telegram"]
.fi
.RE
.PP
A
.I .driftignore
file (one app per line, # for comments) can be placed in your working
directory to exclude apps from tracking.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/drift/config.toml
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/drift/drift.db
SQLite database storing activities, switches, and sessions.
.TP
.I ~/.config/drift/drift.pid
PID file for daemon management.
.TP
.I .driftignore
Per-project ignore file for apps that should not be tracked.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
No environment variables are currently used. All configuration is via
config.toml and .driftignore.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic daily usage:
.B drift daemon start
.br
.B drift status
.br
.B drift report
.TP
Start a 25-minute focus session:
.B drift focus 25
.TP
Compare two days:
.B drift compare \-\-date1 2026-07-20 \-\-date2 2026-07-21
.TP
Compare week-over-week:
.B drift compare \-\-week
.TP
Export today's data as CSV:
.B drift export \-f csv \-d 2026-07-23
.TP
Apply the development preset:
.B drift preset development
.TP
Add an app to .driftignore:
.B drift ignore add spotify
.TP
Generate bash completions:
.B drift completions bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/drift
.TP
Export config to a file:
.B drift export-config \-o my-config.json
.TP
Import config from a file:
.B drift import my-config.json
